Job Summary:
 
Principal Duties and Responsibilities: 
Develop and produce high quality and well-documented code for our computer-aided physician documentation platform primarily in Ruby on Rails. 
Collaborate with Product Management and peer software engineers to design, develop, and implement features for our AI based Computer Assisted Physician Documentation solutions. 
Work with Product Management to analyze product requirements and customer needs, to help write both functional and technical specifications for application components as well as major features/versions. 
Participate in all phases of the software development and testing cycle as part of a multi-functional Scrum team. 
Implement and maintain both unit tests and automated functional test coverage in collaboration with other Scrum team members. 
Ability to learn and adapt new technologies quickly. 
Qualifications: 
Education :   Bachelor of Science in Computer Science or equivalent 
1+ year Ruby and Ruby on Rails experience 
Required Skills: 
Practical experience in Ruby on Rails 
Familiar with SQL 
Familiar with a hosted platform, such as Azure or AWS 
Good written and verbal communication skills 
Ability to work well both within and across Scrum teams 
Preferred Skills : 
Experience using Jira / Git or similar tools 
Javascript, React a plus 
Experience with distributed systems using HTTP/REST, WebSockets a plus 
Additional Information:
 
Nuance offers a compelling and rewarding work environment. We offer market competitive salaries, bonus, equity, benefits, meaningful growth and development opportunities and a casual yet technically challenging work environment. Join our dynamic, entrepreneurial team and become part of our continuing success. 
